## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Contest Analytics frontend application.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
1. `package.json` - Added `@vercel/analytics` ^2.0.1 as a dependency
2. `package-lock.json` - Updated with the new package and its dependencies
3. `src/App.tsx` - Added Analytics component integration

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics documentation (retrieved from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:

1. **Installed the package:** Used npm to install `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1
2. **Added the import:** Imported the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
3. **Integrated the component:** Added `<Analytics />` to the root App component, placed at the end of the main container div

### Framework-Specific Configuration

This is a React + Vite project using TypeScript. The Analytics component was added using the React-specific import path (`@vercel/analytics/react`) as specified in the documentation for React applications.

The Analytics component is a wrapper around the tracking script that provides seamless integration with React. It was added to the App component, which is the root component of the application, ensuring analytics tracking is enabled across all routes.

### Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ TypeScript compilation passed
- ✅ All dependencies properly installed (177 packages added)
- ✅ No breaking changes to existing functionality

### Next Steps

To enable analytics data collection:
1. Deploy this project to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Navigate to the Analytics tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics
4. After deployment and user visits, data will be visible in the dashboard

The Analytics component will automatically begin tracking page views once the application is deployed to Vercel and analytics is enabled in the dashboard.
